parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of airbags to deploy can lead to serious injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Airbags did not deploy in an accident
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delayed or unavailable repairs for Takata airbag recalls can lead to continued risk of injury or fatalities.
symptoms: Difficulty scheduling repairs
unavailability of parts
lack of communication from dealerships or manufacturers
and continued risk of injury or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
grinding or slipping sounds when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift into gear
the transmission slips or grinds when shifting gears
the vehicle loses power or speed
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the accelerator pedal can cause the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the vehicle is difficult to control or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shifter can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The gear shifter is difficult to move or stuck
the vehicle hesitates or refuses to shift into gear
the transmission slips or grinds when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without pressing the gas pedal
and may not respond to braking attempts. The engine RPMs may increase rapidly
and the vehicle may continue to accelerate even when the driver attempts to slow down or stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck accelerator pedal can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal becomes stuck or stuck open
causing the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably. The driver may not be able to stop or slow down the vehicle
even when pressing the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning electronic throttle control can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's electronic throttle control system fails
causing the throttle to become stuck open or stuck closed
leading to unintended acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Floor mat interference can cause the accelerator pedal to become stuck, leading to unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The floor mat becomes lodged under the accelerator pedal
causing it to become stuck or stuck open
leading to unintended acceleration.
